    Input 2 - The finding with title and description in JSON format to be verified. 
    <finding>
    {"title": "start_tge accepts external mints that may retain privileged authorities after TGE", "description": "Root cause & mechanism\nThe TGE entrypoint start_tge() treats a caller-supplied Token-2022 mint as the project\u2019s canonical distribution asset, but it only enforces a narrow invariant: the mint\u2019s mint authority must be the program\u2019s master_pda (#[account(mut, mint::authority = master_pda)]). It does not cryptographically/statefully bind the lifecycle to a single program-created \u201ccanonical\u201d mint nor validate that the provided mint has a pristine, expected configuration.\n\nAs a result, start_tge() performs critical one-time actions on potentially arbitrary or non-standard mints:\n- It unconditionally mints TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY (described as the full ~25B issuance) via token_2022::mint_to(..., TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY) into the \u201cmaster vault\u201d ATA (master_ata).\n- It immediately revokes only AuthorityType::MintTokens by calling token_2022::set_authority(..., AuthorityType::MintTokens, None), but does not validate/clear other privileged controls or Token-2022 extensions that can retain power after TGE (e.g., freeze authority, Permanent Delegate).\n- It distributes liquid allocations using token_2022::transfer_checked for MARKETING_LIQUID_SUPPLY, LIQUIDITY_LIQUID_SUPPLY, and RESERVE_LIQUID_SUPPLY + RESERVE_PADDING, and other flows (category releases, investor claims) also rely on transfer_checked while updating vesting/accounting state as if transfers are always 1:1.\n\nCompounding this, production builds rely on externally prepared mints because initialize_mint is only compiled under #[cfg(feature = \"local-testing\")]. That makes it feasible to pass an externally created Token-2022 mint into start_tge as long as its mint authority is set to master_pda, even if the mint already has supply, has non-1:1 transfer semantics (TransferFeeConfig), or retains other privileged authorities/extensions.\n\nTrigger conditions / assumptions\n- Non-local-testing/production deployment where initialize_mint is not available, so mint preparation is performed externally/off-chain.\n- A privileged caller (\u201cmaster signer\u201d / multisig admin) provides a Token-2022 mint that satisfies mint::authority = master_pda, but where one or more of the following are true:\n  1) The mint is not fresh (mint.supply > 0 and/or tokens already exist in external holders\u2019 accounts).\n  2) The master_ata vault already has a non-zero balance prior to TGE.\n  3) The mint includes Token-2022 extensions with non-standard semantics, especially TransferFeeConfig (recipients receive less than the requested amount even though CPI succeeds).\n  4) The mint retains privileged controls beyond minting, such as a freeze authority or extensions like Permanent Delegate, allowing post-TGE freezing/moving/burning of balances by a third party.\n  5) The mint was created outside the program\u2019s intended initialization/metadata-bound path; categories can still be initialized because category PDAs are effectively namespaced by the caller-supplied mint.key().\n- Investor/category preconditions checked in start_tge are satisfied (e.g., has_enough_investors for pre_seed_cat and seed_cat), and ATAs match the computed associated addresses for the provided mint.\n\nImpact\n- Irreversible over-minting / inflation: If the supplied mint already has any pre-existing supply (or if master_ata is pre-funded), start_tge mints TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY on top of that, causing total circulating supply to exceed the intended hard cap (TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY). This bad state is then finalized because mint authority is revoked immediately after mint_to, leaving no way to correct supply through the program\u2019s minting controls.\n- Wrong-mint finalization and fragmented issuance: Because the program does not enforce a unique canonical mint address, multiple different Token-2022 mints can be \u201cblessed\u201d (categories initialized + TGE executed). A privileged operator can accidentally or maliciously run TGE against an unintended mint, permanently canonizing the wrong asset by minting TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY and revoking mint authority.\n- Vesting/delivery accounting breaks under non-1:1 transfers: If the mint has TransferFeeConfig, transfer_checked calls can succeed while destinations receive less than intended (e.g., less than MARKETING_LIQUID_SUPPLY / LIQUIDITY_LIQUID_SUPPLY / monthly category allocations / investor claim amounts). Meanwhile, the program advances vesting state (months_claimed, tokens_ready_for_claim, investor.vesting_months_remaining) as if full amounts were delivered, permanently underfunding beneficiaries and potentially marking schedules as fully progressed despite underpayment.\n- Post-TGE privileged third-party control: Even though minting is disabled by revoking AuthorityType::MintTokens, other retained authorities/extensions (freeze authority, Permanent Delegate) can enable a third party to freeze token accounts or move/burn distributed balances after TGE, violating the vesting program\u2019s trust model.\n\nExploitation / reproduction notes (PoC highlights)\nA. Over-minting / double-issue\n1) In production, create or reuse a Token-2022 mint externally.\n2) Mint any non-zero amount to any account(s) (creating preexisting supply and possibly external holders) and/or pre-fund master_ata.\n3) Transfer the mint authority of that mint to the program\u2019s master_pda.\n4) Call start_tge with this mint and the expected ATAs.\n5) Observe: start_tge still mints TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY into master_ata and revokes mint authority, resulting in total supply = preexisting_supply + TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY (permanent hard-cap break).\n\nB. Wrong-mint canonization / parallel namespace\n1) Create an external Token-2022 mint (not via the intended program initialization/metadata binding) with mint authority set to master_pda.\n2) Initialize investor/functional category accounts for that specific mint.key() (categories are namespaced by the provided mint) and satisfy has_enough_investors checks.\n3) Provide ATAs that match get_associated_token_address_with_program_id(..., &mint.key(), &token_2022::ID).\n4) Call start_tge; it will mint TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY, revoke mint authority, set cliff_started_at for multiple categories, and transfer initial liquid supplies\u2014treating this external mint as canonical.\n\nC. Underpayment via transfer fees\n1) Create an external Token-2022 mint with TransferFeeConfig enabled; set mint authority to master_pda.\n2) Run start_tge and later category releases/investor claims.\n3) Transfers via transfer_checked succeed, but recipients receive less than the program-accounted amounts, while months_claimed/tokens_ready_for_claim/investor.vesting_months_remaining continue to advance as if fully paid.\n\nD. Retained privileged authorities\n1) Create an external Token-2022 mint whose mint authority is master_pda but which retains freeze authority and/or an extension such as Permanent Delegate controlled by a third party.\n2) Run start_tge; it only revokes AuthorityType::MintTokens.\n3) After TGE, the third party can freeze token accounts or move/burn balances despite minting being disabled.\n\nCode-location anchors (from inputs)\n- File: programs/master-token-program/src/instructions/tge.rs\n- Instruction/handler: pub fn start_tge<'info>(ctx: Context<'_, '_, '_, 'info, Tge<'info>>) -> Result<()>\n- Mint constraint (only): #[account(mut, mint::authority = master_pda)] pub mint: Box<InterfaceAccount<'info, Mint>>;\n- ATA checks are address-only (not emptiness/supply/config): require_keys_eq!(..., get_associated_token_address_with_program_id(..., &ctx.accounts.mint.key(), &token_2022::ID), ErrorCode::AtaMismatch) for master_ata/marketing_ata/liquidity_ata/reserve_ata\n- Unconditional full issuance: token_2022::mint_to(..., TOTAL_MINT_SUPPLY)\n- Only minting authority revoked: token_2022::set_authority(..., AuthorityType::MintTokens, None)\n- Liquid distribution transfers: token_2022::transfer_checked(..., MARKETING_LIQUID_SUPPLY, SBT_DECIMALS); similarly LIQUIDITY_LIQUID_SUPPLY and RESERVE_LIQUID_SUPPLY + RESERVE_PADDING\n- Vesting/accounting assumptions around transfer_checked (as provided): updates to category.months_claimed, category.tokens_ready_for_claim, and investor.vesting_months_remaining occur as if transfers deliver the full requested total_tokens\n- Investor readiness checks during TGE: require!(has_enough_investors(&pre_seed_cat, PRE_SEED_CATEGORY.pre_investors), ErrorCode::UnintializedInvestors) and similarly for seed_cat\n- Production-only gap: initialize_mint exists only under #[cfg(feature = \"local-testing\")], so production relies on externally prepared mints."}
    </finding>

